annotation.TEXT: Yeah, it's collapsing.
It was probably difficult for you to see, but the "1-up" got replaced with "PWNED" there. I'm guessing it was a trap, but I was still fast enough to reach the next star anyway.
It's a castle, so no Yoshis allowed (not that I've seen any Yoshis around here).
To be continued... Ooh, treasure!
And now we've got Cave Story music, and the stars don't interrupt the music this time around. That's neat.
Another star...
Oh, it was a "queen"? Sorry, I assumed it was a guy at first. It's hard to tell the gender of some species...

I'm glad the normal music doesn't get interrupted by the stars in this hack. Listening to the star music would probably get old after a while, especially if you have to repeat a level due to failures or something.
I'm assuming those red bridge tiles collapse just like the purple ones from before.
And we're still at this level (but it doesn't have the period at the end of its name this time). Let's enter it and see what happens.
A goal sphere! I guess I made it! But, what happens to the island now?
Insert overused DBZ meme here.
Hello, and welcome to...
These purple bridge blocks shatter on contact and bounce you up a little bit. Be careful.
I'm going to wait a bit before grabbing the star.

So basically, we're pretty much going through the same level from the first game, but backwards, and on a short time limit. Also, there are a few level modifications here and there to make going backwards possible.
Whoa, I just barely made that!
The screen is supposed to be shaking constantly here, but if you can't see it, I blame YouTube's forced 30 FPS frame rate.
There are added blocks here to allow me to climb up.
Seems like a ghost ship, but with a ton of munchers in it.
But what possibly insane challenges await in this new level?
Ooh, a 1-up! ...Wait a minute...
Oh, no! That big muncher I defeated last time must've been a load-bearing boss!
The screen doesn't scroll any further to the right there, so let's go up and left.
I thought about repeatedly stomping bullet munchers for lives there, but decided not to bother right now. If I need lives later for some reason, I'll come back.
Yeah, that was a miss. Why only its left side is vulnerable is beyond me. (I think this was the case with the other such boss as well.)
And thus, we arrive at The Muncher Kingdom, which is on a muncher shaped island with munchers on it.
Ahh! AHH!!! What do I do? What do I do? What do I do?! (Also, apparently this music is a crazy remix of Chocolate Rain. I guess I can sort of hear it...)
I guess I'm going down here.
Yay for a pointless block clone!
The cement blocks around here have collapsed a bit, which is good, because I needed a way to get over this wall.
Well, I got one life. I was hoping I could squeeze in a second one though.
Uh, oh. I hope I don't need that shell anymore...
Anyway, this battle works the same as the last one, except the koopas pop out to the right, not the left.
Larry's castle, is that you? It certainly seems like it's a blatant level edit of Larry's castle, but instead of a block snake, we've got munchers!
The jumps around here have changed quite a bit.
Whoa! Thank you invisible coin block! I think I would've bounced right into the munchers there if it wasn't there!
Now loading... Wait, what?
Ooh, a missing corner tile in the upper-left! Also, there's a shell and a star here. I guess I'm supposed to speed through this area.
Make sure you aim the shells at the big guy's left side to make sure you hit him. They may not register as a hit if they just touch its right side.
No P-switch or control coin for me this time.
And that's it for this level. The screen doesn't scroll very far in either direction, so just grab the goal sphere.
Definitely had to ditch the ice block there.
Got him! Yeah! Also, don't worry too much about the leftover koopas. Once the victory music starts, they can't harm you.
Is this the exit?
And there's the new island over there on the right. You can access it by moving to the right from OMNOMNOcean.
Whoa, that was really close!
Also, we've got more crazy music going on here! Is this another Chocolate Rain remix? It's hard to tell...
Possibly tricky spring jump. Try to hit the right edge of the springboard.
Ooh, lucky! I happened to finish with exactly 100 seconds left, which gives me a free life since I have no bonus stars!
Oh, we've got a thunderstorm going on. Yeah, this planet's gonna explode soon, so I need to get to Samus's ship fast! (Wait, wrong game. I just need to get off this island in time. That's all.)
Yes! Good thing for the note blocks around here!
Munchers composing music on Mario Paint! No, actually, it's...
I don't know why the screen remained black for several seconds there.
Huh. Before I enter the next level, is it possible to replay that first level?
Also, apparently there's another island to explore...
Ooh, so now the munchers are all nuclear powered, or something. Well, let's start the game!
Nope, it's not letting me in. Well, I had to check, since the level dot was still there. Also, you can move the map around with Start this time.
And there's ice blocks that I've gotta clear out, so I probably was supposed to ditch the shell anyway. That's good. Hey, can I possibly get a 1-up chain here?
...The Muncher Run 2! It's the sequel to The Muncher Run, created by Ersanomnom again, and also Bad Luck Manomnom this time I guess.
The bullets are still just as useless as ever. (You could try chain killing them while invincible for points and lives, but I seriously don't think that's a good idea.)
Oh, and when a star is about to run out, it makes the "P-switch is expiring" sound effect, which is a nice touch.
Also, munchers are being fired at me! However, they're just basically Bullet Bills, and can be stomped.
Could it possibly be... boss time?
It's pretty straightforward at this point, and the stars are all in the same places here.
MOOOOOONNN!!! I SAW IT, SO I MUST HAVE IT!!!
Well, let's enter the next level, OMNOMNOcean.
No turn blocks to break through here, which is good, since I'm small!
Well, let's explore this place...

I actually half-expected that hidden coin block. At least hitting this hidden coin block doesn't result in me plunging to my death, unlike a certain well-known hack that siryoshi427 is currently playing through!
These jumps aren't anything that I can't handle.
Find out next timenomnomnom!
AHH!!! It's the ghost of the big muncher I beat up back on Muncher Island! Or maybe it's just a palette swap twin. Who knows?
